  "title": "Chef De Partie (Cafe)",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for an experienced Chef de Partie (Cafe) to lead the brunch station and ensure that every cafe item is executed to standards of quality and consistency.<br /></p><p><strong>Location & Work Hours</strong></p><ul><li>Toa Payoh</li><li>5 day work week</li><li>8 work hours straight shifts with 1 hour meal break</li><li>Shift timing starts at 8am - 10am depending on schedule</li><li>Rotating rest days</li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Prepare, cook, assemble, and present artisanal sandos, brunch dishes, and deli plates according to Creamier’s recipes and standards.</p></li><li><p>Oversee the deli station and ensure smooth operations during service.</p></li><li><p>Supervise and guide food prep team, providing support and coaching.</p></li><li><p>Ensure all mise-en-place is completed accurately and on time.</p></li><li><p>Maintain high standards of cleanliness, hygiene, and food safety in the kitchen.</p></li><li><p>Monitor stock levels, assist in ordering, and support inventory management.</p></li><li><p>Contribute to menu planning, specials, and new dish development, especially for sandos and brunch.</p></li><li><p>Ensure proper use, care, and maintenance of all deli and kitchen equipment.</p></li><li><p>Assist the Sous Chef with overall kitchen operations during service.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><p>Proven experience as a Chef de Partie, or strong Demi Chef ready to step up.</p></li><li><p>Strong teamwork, communication, and time-management skills.</p></li><li><p>Passionate about artisanal food and delivering consistent quality.</p></li><li><p>Positive attitude, willingness to learn, and strong attention to detail.</p></li></ul>",
